{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CiCDSiysHdN8ZDpqjiC654","type":"tool_result","content":"1500\t  test --run` ✅ (267/267, no regressions). The dedicated query +\n1501\t  page tests for `/games/[game]` are scheduled as the third item in\n1502\t  the FR-8 per-game block and will exercise the four stuck filters,\n1503\t  refunds, sparse data, and all three games end-to-end.\n1504\t\n1505\t\n1506\t## Iteration 33 — 2026-04-25T13:04:43Z — OK\n1507\t- **Log**: iteration-033.log\n1508\t\n1509\t\n1510\t\n1511\t## Iteration 34 — 2026-04-25\n1512\t\n1513\t- FR-8 frontend half: the `/games/[game]` route. One Next.js dynamic\n1514\t  segment that resolves `flipyou`, `potshot`, and `closecall` and\n1515\t  notFounds anything else (validated against `PEEK_GAME_IDS`). Page is\n1516\t  role-gated through `getPeekActorContext` + `isRouteAllowedForRole`\n1517\t  the same way `/games` is, so unknown roles render the existing\n1518\t  access-denied alert without leaking the table.\n1519\t- Two server-side branches inside the page:\n1520\t  - FlipYou + Pot Shot share `listRounds({ game })` and render\n1521\t    `GameRoundsTable`. The `[game]` param is statically narrowed to\n1522\t    `'flipyou' | 'potshot'` before the call so TypeScript enforces the\n1523\t    `PeekRoundsGameId` constraint introduced in iteration 33; Close\n1524\t    Call cannot be passed to `listRounds` even by accident.\n1525\t  - Close Call calls `listCloseCallRounds()` and renders\n1526\t    `CloseCallRoundsTable`. Different table because the column set\n1527\t    (open/close prices, expo, green/red pools, total fee, outcome) and\n1528\t    the lifecycle (`open` -> `settled`/`refunded`) differ from the\n1529\t    shared `rounds` table.\n1530\t- New `peek/src/lib/games-search-params.ts`:\n1531\t  - `normalizeRoundFiltersFromSearchParams` produces a\n1532\t    `PeekRoundFilters` from raw Next.js search params (`phase`,\n1533\t    `search`, `fromDate`, `toDate`, plus the four stuck booleans\n1534\t    `stuckAged`, `stuckAttempts`, `stuckNoTx`, `stuckRefunds`).\n1535\t    Phase passes through only if it matches `PEEK_ROUND_PHASES` so\n1536\t    a bogus URL value falls back to \"any phase\" instead of producing\n1537\t    a SQL match-nothing filter.\n1538\t  - `normalizeCloseCallRoundFiltersFromSearchParams` mirrors the same\n1539\t    shape minus `stuckAttempts` (closecall has no settle_attempts\n1540\t    column) and adds an `outcome` field validated against\n1541\t    `PEEK_CLOSECALL_OUTCOMES`.\n1542\t  - `readPageFromSearchParams` clamps non-numeric / non-positive page\n1543\t    params to `1`. The query module already clamps server-side; this\n1544\t    keeps the link the navigation renders honest.\n1545\t  - `buildRoundsQueryString` rebuilds the query string for pagination\n1546\t    links and preserves every passthrough filter so navigating to page\n1547\t    2 does not silently drop the operator's filter state.\n1548\t- New `peek/src/components/game-rounds-filter-bar.tsx`:\n1549\t  - Discriminated-union props on the `game` literal so the same form\n1550\t    component renders the right shape for FlipYou+Pot Shot vs Close\n1551\t    Call without a runtime conditional. The `outcome` dropdown only\n1552\t    renders when `game === 'closecall'`; the `stuckAttempts` checkbox\n1553\t    only renders for FlipYou+Pot Shot. Default values are reflected\n1554\t    from the parsed filter object so the form is shareable via URL.\n1555\t  - Stuck filters render as a `<fieldset>` with a labelled\n1556\t    `<legend>` (\"Stuck-state filters\") so screen readers and inline\n1557\t    HTML inspection both make the grouping obvious.\n1558\t- New `peek/src/components/game-rounds-table.tsx`\n1559\t  (FlipYou + Pot Shot) and\n1560\t  `peek/src/components/closecall-rounds-table.tsx` (Close Call):\n1561\t  - Dense tables with columns matching the FR-8 acceptance criteria:\n1562\t    `rounds` (phase, pda, match id, creator, target slot, settle\n1563\t    attempts, settle tx, result side, winner, timestamps) and\n1564\t    `closecall_rounds` (phase, outcome, pda, prices, pools, fee,\n1565\t    settle tx, timestamps). Lamports / u64 strings format with\n1566\t    thousands separators while preserving the `\"0\"` literal for\n1567\t    measured zeros (FR-4).\n1568\t  - Phase + outcome render through the existing `StatusChip` so\n1569\t    refunded / expired / settled states pop visually without a\n1570\t    chart library; tone mapping mirrors the spec's exception-first\n1571\t    framing (settled => positive, refund/expired => warning).\n1572\t  - Long pubkeys (pda, creator, winner, settle_tx, match_id, round_id)\n1573\t    truncate with a unicode ellipsis and keep the full string in the\n1574\t    `title` attribute so an operator can read the full value on hover\n1575\t    without exporting the row.\n1576\t  - Empty + error states render inline (`role=\"status\"` /\n1577\t    `role=\"alert\"`), matching the existing `GamesOverviewTable` and\n1578\t    `GrowthClaimsTable` conventions.\n1579\t- The page assembles a small page header with a `← Games` breadcrumb,\n1580\t  a `Filters` section, a `Rounds` section with row/total/page hint and\n1581\t  `Previous`/`Next` pagination links, and surfaces query errors inline\n1582\t  so a transient DB failure does not nuke the route. The pagination\n1583\t  links go through `buildRoundsQueryString` so filter state survives\n1584\t  page navigation.\n1585\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅, `pnpm\n1586\t  test --run` ✅ (267/267, no regressions). The dedicated query +\n1587\t  page tests for `/games/[game]` (FR-8 stuck filters, refunds, sparse\n1588\t  data, all 3 games) are the next checklist item.\n1589\t\n1590\t## Iteration 34 — 2026-04-25T13:11:26Z — OK\n1591\t- **Log**: iteration-034.log\n1592\t\n1593\t\n1594\t\n1595\t## Iteration 35 — 2026-04-25\n1596\t\n1597\t- FR-8 test gate: dedicated query + view tests for `/games/[game]` covering\n1598\t  all three games, the four stuck-state booleans, refund states, and sparse\n1599\t  data. Five new test files (67 new tests total; suite now 334/334):\n1600\t  - `peek/src/server/db/queries/__tests__/get-game-rounds.test.ts` —\n1601\t    `listRounds` + `listCloseCallRounds`. Re-uses the\n1602\t    `createSqlMock`/queued-response pattern from the games-overview and\n1603\t    growth-referrals tests so the engine surface stays consistent. Covers:\n1604\t    populated row shaping (incl. a u64 lamport amount > MAX_SAFE_INTEGER),\n1605\t    the `flipyou` vs `potshot` SQL pivot, defense-in-depth filtering of\n1606\t    out-of-band game ids (e.g. a future `crash` row), sparse + 1-logical-page\n1607\t    behaviour, the phase / search / date filter parameter binding, all four\n1608\t    stuck flags (nonterminalAged binds the age interval; highAttempts binds\n1609\t    the maxSettleAttempts threshold; settledWithoutTx asserts the correlated\n1610\t    `not exists` over `transactions`; refunds asserts `phase = 'expired'`),\n1611\t    the no-stuck short-circuit, pagination clamping (page = -3 -> 1, pageSize\n1612\t    = 99999 -> `PEEK_GAME_ROUNDS_MAX_PAGE_SIZE`), Postgres `::text` count\n1613\t    coercion, settleAttempts/resultSide string coercion, and load-error\n1614\t    propagation from either parallel query. Close Call coverage adds: phase\n1615\t    + outcome dual-filter binding, the `t.game = 'closecall'` hard-coding in\n1616\t    the NOT EXISTS subquery (cc has no `r.game` join column), the `phase =\n1617\t    'refunded' OR outcome = 'refund'` refund predicate (the migration allows\n1618\t    a settled row to carry a `refund` outcome before the phase transition\n1619\t    lands, so checking either captures the operator-visible state),\n1620\t    nonterminalAged on `phase = 'open'` with override threshold, and the\n1621\t    Pyth `openPriceExpo` integer coercion from the postgres string.\n1622\t  - `peek/src/components/__tests__/game-rounds-table.test.tsx` — populated\n1623\t    rendering of every FR-8 column for FlipYou+Pot Shot, lamport thousands\n1624\t    formatting, em-dash placeholders for null target slot/settleTx/winner/\n1625\t    settledAt, StatusChip integration per phase, full-value `title=`\n1626\t    on truncated pubkeys, refund-row (phase=`expired`) operator visibility,\n1627\t    sparse empty-state pointing at the `rounds` table, and error-alert\n1628\t    state suppressing both the table and the empty status.\n1629\t  - `peek/src/components/__tests__/closecall-rounds-table.test.tsx` —\n1630\t    populated Close Call rendering with the Pyth `expo -8` sublabel, all\n1631\t    twelve column headers, phase + outcome dual chips (open / settled /\n1632\t    refunded × pending / green / red / refund), `title=` audit hover for\n1633\t    long pubkeys, an open-round null-set asserting at least 3 em-dashes\n1634\t    (closePrice + settleTx + settledAt), the refunded+refund composite\n1635\t    refund row, the sparse state pointing at `closecall_rounds`, and the\n1636\t    error-alert state.\n1637\t  - `peek/src/components/__tests__/game-rounds-filter-bar.test.tsx` — the\n1638\t    discriminated-union form. FlipYou + Pot Shot variant: blank-form state\n1639\t    with the `phase` whitelist matching `PEEK_ROUND_PHASES`, populated state\n1640\t    reflecting every filter value back into the input, Pot Shot's aria\n1641\t    label, the missing `Outcome` dropdown (rounds table has no Pyth\n1642\t    outcome), and the `name` attributes aligning with\n1643\t    `normalizeRoundFiltersFromSearchParams`. Close Call variant: phase +\n1644\t    outcome whitelists per `PEEK_CLOSECALL_PHASES` /\n1645\t    `PEEK_CLOSECALL_OUTCOMES`, the missing `High settle attempts` checkbox\n1646\t    (closecall has no `settle_attempts` column), populated state, and the\n1647\t    `outcome` input name contract.\n1648\t  - `peek/src/lib/__tests__/games-search-params.test.ts` —\n1649\t    `normalizeRoundFiltersFromSearchParams`,\n1650\t    `normalizeCloseCallRoundFiltersFromSearchParams`,\n1651\t    `readPageFromSearchParams`, and `buildRoundsQueryString`. Covers\n1652\t    empty / whitespace / undefined / array (Next.js repeated-param) inputs,\n1653\t    the phase + outcome whitelist falling back to `null` instead of\n1654\t    producing a SQL match-nothing filter, the boolean checkbox semantics\n1655\t    (`1`/`true`/`on`/`yes`), the Close Call shape never carrying\n1656\t    `highAttempts` even if the URL passes `stuckAttempts`, page clamping\n1657\t    (`\"\"`, `\"   \"`, `\"0\"`, `\"-3\"`, `\"abc\"` → `1`), and\n1658\t    `buildRoundsQueryString` preserving every filter passthrough,\n1659\t    canonically dropping `page=1`, dropping whitespace-only passthroughs,\n1660\t    and appending `page=N` when N>1.\n1661\t- One small test fix during the run: `screen.getByText(\"0\")` collided with\n1662\t  the multiple \"0\" cells the table renders for a settling row (resultSide,\n1663\t  amountLamports). Switched to\n1664\t  `screen.getAllByText(\"0\").length).toBeGreaterThan(0)` — same operator\n1665\t  signal, doesn't couple to the exact column count.\n1666\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅, `pnpm test\n1667\t  --run` ✅ (334/334; +67 tests).\n1668\t## Iteration 35 — 2026-04-25T13:20:30Z — OK\n1669\t- **Log**: iteration-035.log\n1670\t\n1671\t\n1672\t\n1673\t## Iteration 36 — 2026-04-25\n1674\t\n1675\t- FR-8 engine: round detail query joining `rounds` (FlipYou + Pot Shot) or\n1676\t  `closecall_rounds` (Close Call) with `game_entries` (per-round\n1677\t  participants) and `transactions` (per-round on-chain SOL movements).\n1678\t- New `peek/src/server/db/queries/get-round-detail.ts`:\n1679\t  - `getRoundDetail({ game, roundId })` — `roundId` is the on-chain `pda`\n1680\t    for all 3 games so the future `/games/[game]/rounds/[roundId]` route\n1681\t    has a uniform URL shape.\n1682\t  - Looks up the round summary by `pda` in the appropriate table, then\n1683\t    fetches entries (by `round_pda`) and transactions (by `match_id` +\n1684\t    `game`) in parallel via `Promise.all`. Returns `null` when the round\n1685\t    isn't found.\n1686\t  - Close Call branch resolves transactions through the round's\n1687\t    `round_id` (the migration uses the round id as `transactions.match_id`\n1688\t    for closecall) and hard-codes `t.game = 'closecall'` to match the\n1689\t    existing list-rounds query.\n1690\t  - FlipYou + Pot Shot branch double-binds `game` in addition to `pda`\n1691\t    so a stale URL with the wrong game param can't surface a row from the\n1692\t    other game; defense-in-depth `isPeekRoundsGameId` check after\n1693\t    normalization filters out any out-of-band `r.game` value (e.g. a\n1694\t    future migration row).\n1695\t  - All u64/precision-sensitive values round-trip as `text` (lamport\n1696\t    sums, target slot, prices); slot/result_side parse to integers via\n1697\t    the same `readInt` helper used in `get-game-rounds.ts`.\n1698\t- New view models in `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`:\n1699\t  - `PeekRoundEntryRow` — operator-readable shape with `userId`,\n1700\t    `username` (LEFT JOIN `player_profiles`, null when absent), `wallet`,\n1701\t    `amountLamports`, `side`, `isWinner`, `payoutLamports`, `createdAt`,\n1702\t    `settledAt`. Distinct from the user-detail `PeekGameEntryRow` because\n1703\t    the round-detail page renders participants (so it needs identity\n1704\t    columns) instead of a single user's recent entries.\n1705\t  - `PeekRoundTransactionRow` — same identity treatment for the\n1706\t    `transactions` join (txType, amountLamports, txSig, createdAt).\n1707\t  - `PeekRoundDetail` — discriminated union on `game`. The\n1708\t    `flipyou`/`potshot` branch carries `PeekRoundRow`; the `closecall`\n1709\t    branch carries `PeekCloseCallRoundRow`. Entries + transactions are\n1710\t    shared shapes since both tables produce the same operator surface.\n1711\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅, `pnpm test\n1712\t  --run` ✅ (334/334, no regressions). The page + dedicated round-detail\n1713\t  query/page tests are the next two FR-8 items.\n1714\t## Iteration 36 — 2026-04-25T13:25:30Z — OK\n1715\t- **Log**: iteration-036.log"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e7393274-dd95-4a47-827c-0160987ea587","uuid":"00623ebe-1912-4643-a57b-24c0c024131f","timestamp":"2026-04-25T13:25:52.886Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/305-peek-operations-admin/history.md","content":"  test --run` ✅ (267/267, no regressions). The dedicated query +\n  page tests for `/games/[game]` are scheduled as the third item in\n  the FR-8 per-game block and will exercise the four stuck filters,\n  refunds, sparse data, and all three games end-to-end.\n\n\n## Iteration 33 — 2026-04-25T13:04:43Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-033.log\n\n\n\n## Iteration 34 — 2026-04-25\n\n- FR-8 frontend half: the `/games/[game]` route. One Next.js dynamic\n  segment that resolves `flipyou`, `potshot`, and `closecall` and\n  notFounds anything else (validated against `PEEK_GAME_IDS`). Page is\n  role-gated through `getPeekActorContext` + `isRouteAllowedForRole`\n  the same way `/games` is, so unknown roles render the existing\n  access-denied alert without leaking the table.\n- Two server-side branches inside the page:\n  - FlipYou + Pot Shot share `listRounds({ game })` and render\n    `GameRoundsTable`. The `[game]` param is statically narrowed to\n    `'flipyou' | 'potshot'` before the call so TypeScript enforces the\n    `PeekRoundsGameId` constraint introduced in iteration 33; Close\n    Call cannot be passed to `listRounds` even by accident.\n  - Close Call calls `listCloseCallRounds()` and renders\n    `CloseCallRoundsTable`. Different table because the column set\n    (open/close prices, expo, green/red pools, total fee, outcome) and\n    the lifecycle (`open` -> `settled`/`refunded`) differ from the\n    shared `rounds` table.\n- New `peek/src/lib/games-search-params.ts`:\n  - `normalizeRoundFiltersFromSearchParams` produces a\n    `PeekRoundFilters` from raw Next.js search params (`phase`,\n    `search`, `fromDate`, `toDate`, plus the four stuck booleans\n    `stuckAged`, `stuckAttempts`, `stuckNoTx`, `stuckRefunds`).\n    Phase passes through only if it matches `PEEK_ROUND_PHASES` so\n    a bogus URL value falls back to \"any phase\" instead of producing\n    a SQL match-nothing filter.\n  - `normalizeCloseCallRoundFiltersFromSearchParams` mirrors the same\n    shape minus `stuckAttempts` (closecall has no settle_attempts\n    column) and adds an `outcome` field validated against\n    `PEEK_CLOSECALL_OUTCOMES`.\n  - `readPageFromSearchParams` clamps non-numeric / non-positive page\n    params to `1`. The query module already clamps server-side; this\n    keeps the link the navigation renders honest.\n  - `buildRoundsQueryString` rebuilds the query string for pagination\n    links and preserves every passthrough filter so navigating to page\n    2 does not silently drop the operator's filter state.\n- New `peek/src/components/game-rounds-filter-bar.tsx`:\n  - Discriminated-union props on the `game` literal so the same form\n    component renders the right shape for FlipYou+Pot Shot vs Close\n    Call without a runtime conditional. The `outcome` dropdown only\n    renders when `game === 'closecall'`; the `stuckAttempts` checkbox\n    only renders for FlipYou+Pot Shot. Default values are reflected\n    from the parsed filter object so the form is shareable via URL.\n  - Stuck filters render as a `<fieldset>` with a labelled\n    `<legend>` (\"Stuck-state filters\") so screen readers and inline\n    HTML inspection both make the grouping obvious.\n- New `peek/src/components/game-rounds-table.tsx`\n  (FlipYou + Pot Shot) and\n  `peek/src/components/closecall-rounds-table.tsx` (Close Call):\n  - Dense tables with columns matching the FR-8 acceptance criteria:\n    `rounds` (phase, pda, match id, creator, target slot, settle\n    attempts, settle tx, result side, winner, timestamps) and\n    `closecall_rounds` (phase, outcome, pda, prices, pools, fee,\n    settle tx, timestamps). Lamports / u64 strings format with\n    thousands separators while preserving the `\"0\"` literal for\n    measured zeros (FR-4).\n  - Phase + outcome render through the existing `StatusChip` so\n    refunded / expired / settled states pop visually without a\n    chart library; tone mapping mirrors the spec's exception-first\n    framing (settled => positive, refund/expired => warning).\n  - Long pubkeys (pda, creator, winner, settle_tx, match_id, round_id)\n    truncate with a unicode ellipsis and keep the full string in the\n    `title` attribute so an operator can read the full value on hover\n    without exporting the row.\n  - Empty + error states render inline (`role=\"status\"` /\n    `role=\"alert\"`), matching the existing `GamesOverviewTable` and\n    `GrowthClaimsTable` conventions.\n- The page assembles a small page header with a `← Games` breadcrumb,\n  a `Filters` section, a `Rounds` section with row/total/page hint and\n  `Previous`/`Next` pagination links, and surfaces query errors inline\n  so a transient DB failure does not nuke the route. The pagination\n  links go through `buildRoundsQueryString` so filter state survives\n  page navigation.\n- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅, `pnpm\n  test --run` ✅ (267/267, no regressions). The dedicated query +\n  page tests for `/games/[game]` (FR-8 stuck filters, refunds, sparse\n  data, all 3 games) are the next checklist item.\n\n## Iteration 34 — 2026-04-25T13:11:26Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-034.log\n\n\n\n## Iteration 35 — 2026-04-25\n\n- FR-8 test gate: dedicated query + view tests for `/games/[game]` covering\n  all three games, the four stuck-state booleans, refund states, and sparse\n  data. Five new test files (67 new tests total; suite now 334/334):\n  - `peek/src/server/db/queries/__tests__/get-game-rounds.test.ts` —\n    `listRounds` + `listCloseCallRounds`. Re-uses the\n    `createSqlMock`/queued-response pattern from the games-overview and\n    growth-referrals tests so the engine surface stays consistent. Covers:\n    populated row shaping (incl. a u64 lamport amount > MAX_SAFE_INTEGER),\n    the `flipyou` vs `potshot` SQL pivot, defense-in-depth filtering of\n    out-of-band game ids (e.g. a future `crash` row), sparse + 1-logical-page\n    behaviour, the phase / search / date filter parameter binding, all four\n    stuck flags (nonterminalAged binds the age interval; highAttempts binds\n    the maxSettleAttempts threshold; settledWithoutTx asserts the correlated\n    `not exists` over `transactions`; refunds asserts `phase = 'expired'`),\n    the no-stuck short-circuit, pagination clamping (page = -3 -> 1, pageSize\n    = 99999 -> `PEEK_GAME_ROUNDS_MAX_PAGE_SIZE`), Postgres `::text` count\n    coercion, settleAttempts/resultSide string coercion, and load-error\n    propagation from either parallel query. Close Call coverage adds: phase\n    + outcome dual-filter binding, the `t.game = 'closecall'` hard-coding in\n    the NOT EXISTS subquery (cc has no `r.game` join column), the `phase =\n    'refunded' OR outcome = 'refund'` refund predicate (the migration allows\n    a settled row to carry a `refund` outcome before the phase transition\n    lands, so checking either captures the operator-visible state),\n    nonterminalAged on `phase = 'open'` with override threshold, and the\n    Pyth `openPriceExpo` integer coercion from the postgres string.\n  - `peek/src/components/__tests__/game-rounds-table.test.tsx` — populated\n    rendering of every FR-8 column for FlipYou+Pot Shot, lamport thousands\n    formatting, em-dash placeholders for null target slot/settleTx/winner/\n    settledAt, StatusChip integration per phase, full-value `title=`\n    on truncated pubkeys, refund-row (phase=`expired`) operator visibility,\n    sparse empty-state pointing at the `rounds` table, and error-alert\n    state suppressing both the table and the empty status.\n  - `peek/src/components/__tests__/closecall-rounds-table.test.tsx` —\n    populated Close Call rendering with the Pyth `expo -8` sublabel, all\n    twelve column headers, phase + outcome dual chips (open / settled /\n    refunded × pending / green / red / refund), `title=` audit hover for\n    long pubkeys, an open-round null-set asserting at least 3 em-dashes\n    (closePrice + settleTx + settledAt), the refunded+refund composite\n    refund row, the sparse state pointing at `closecall_rounds`, and the\n    error-alert state.\n  - `peek/src/components/__tests__/game-rounds-filter-bar.test.tsx` — the\n    discriminated-union form. FlipYou + Pot Shot variant: blank-form state\n    with the `phase` whitelist matching `PEEK_ROUND_PHASES`, populated state\n    reflecting every filter value back into the input, Pot Shot's aria\n    label, the missing `Outcome` dropdown (rounds table has no Pyth\n    outcome), and the `name` attributes aligning with\n    `normalizeRoundFiltersFromSearchParams`. Close Call variant: phase +\n    outcome whitelists per `PEEK_CLOSECALL_PHASES` /\n    `PEEK_CLOSECALL_OUTCOMES`, the missing `High settle attempts` checkbox\n    (closecall has no `settle_attempts` column), populated state, and the\n    `outcome` input name contract.\n  - `peek/src/lib/__tests__/games-search-params.test.ts` —\n    `normalizeRoundFiltersFromSearchParams`,\n    `normalizeCloseCallRoundFiltersFromSearchParams`,\n    `readPageFromSearchParams`, and `buildRoundsQueryString`. Covers\n    empty / whitespace / undefined / array (Next.js repeated-param) inputs,\n    the phase + outcome whitelist falling back to `null` instead of\n    producing a SQL match-nothing filter, the boolean checkbox semantics\n    (`1`/`true`/`on`/`yes`), the Close Call shape never carrying\n    `highAttempts` even if the URL passes `stuckAttempts`, page clamping\n    (`\"\"`, `\"   \"`, `\"0\"`, `\"-3\"`, `\"abc\"` → `1`), and\n    `buildRoundsQueryString` preserving every filter passthrough,\n    canonically dropping `page=1`, dropping whitespace-only passthroughs,\n    and appending `page=N` when N>1.\n- One small test fix during the run: `screen.getByText(\"0\")` collided with\n  the multiple \"0\" cells the table renders for a settling row (resultSide,\n  amountLamports). Switched to\n  `screen.getAllByText(\"0\").length).toBeGreaterThan(0)` — same operator\n  signal, doesn't couple to the exact column count.\n- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅, `pnpm test\n  --run` ✅ (334/334; +67 tests).\n## Iteration 35 — 2026-04-25T13:20:30Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-035.log\n\n\n\n## Iteration 36 — 2026-04-25\n\n- FR-8 engine: round detail query joining `rounds` (FlipYou + Pot Shot) or\n  `closecall_rounds` (Close Call) with `game_entries` (per-round\n  participants) and `transactions` (per-round on-chain SOL movements).\n- New `peek/src/server/db/queries/get-round-detail.ts`:\n  - `getRoundDetail({ game, roundId })` — `roundId` is the on-chain `pda`\n    for all 3 games so the future `/games/[game]/rounds/[roundId]` route\n    has a uniform URL shape.\n  - Looks up the round summary by `pda` in the appropriate table, then\n    fetches entries (by `round_pda`) and transactions (by `match_id` +\n    `game`) in parallel via `Promise.all`. Returns `null` when the round\n    isn't found.\n  - Close Call branch resolves transactions through the round's\n    `round_id` (the migration uses the round id as `transactions.match_id`\n    for closecall) and hard-codes `t.game = 'closecall'` to match the\n    existing list-rounds query.\n  - FlipYou + Pot Shot branch double-binds `game` in addition to `pda`\n    so a stale URL with the wrong game param can't surface a row from the\n    other game; defense-in-depth `isPeekRoundsGameId` check after\n    normalization filters out any out-of-band `r.game` value (e.g. a\n    future migration row).\n  - All u64/precision-sensitive values round-trip as `text` (lamport\n    sums, target slot, prices); slot/result_side parse to integers via\n    the same `readInt` helper used in `get-game-rounds.ts`.\n- New view models in `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`:\n  - `PeekRoundEntryRow` — operator-readable shape with `userId`,\n    `username` (LEFT JOIN `player_profiles`, null when absent), `wallet`,\n    `amountLamports`, `side`, `isWinner`, `payoutLamports`, `createdAt`,\n    `settledAt`. Distinct from the user-detail `PeekGameEntryRow` because\n    the round-detail page renders participants (so it needs identity\n    columns) instead of a single user's recent entries.\n  - `PeekRoundTransactionRow` — same identity treatment for the\n    `transactions` join (txType, amountLamports, txSig, createdAt).\n  - `PeekRoundDetail` — discriminated union on `game`. The\n    `flipyou`/`potshot` branch carries `PeekRoundRow`; the `closecall`\n    branch carries `PeekCloseCallRoundRow`. Entries + transactions are\n    shared shapes since both tables produce the same operator surface.\n- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅, `pnpm test\n  --run` ✅ (334/334, no regressions). The page + dedicated round-detail\n  query/page tests are the next two FR-8 items.\n## Iteration 36 — 2026-04-25T13:25:30Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-036.log","numLines":216,"startLine":1500,"totalLines":1717}}}
